     <div type="edition" xml:lang="kan-Latn" rendition="class:kannada maturity:83215">
         <p>
             <lb n="1"/>śrī-brahmēśvara-dēvaralli ēkāntada-rāmayya basadiya jinan oḍḍavāgi taleyan aridu haḍeda ṭāvu <g type="ddanda">.</g> saṁka-gāvuṇḍaṁ basadiyan oḍeyal īyade āḷuṁ-kudureya
             <lb n="2"/>n oḍḍiralu ēkāntada rāmayyaṁ kādi geldu jinan oḍedu liṅga pratiṣṭeyaṁ māḍida ṭāvu
         </p>
     </div>
     
        <div type="translation" resp="Fleet">
            <p n="1-2">This is the place representing how, at <supplied reason="subaudible">the temple of</supplied> the illustration god Brahmēśvara laid a wager, at the cost of the Jina of the shrine, of cutting off his head and received it back again. When Saṅka-gāvuṇḍa would not let him destroy the shrine of the Jina arraying his men and horses against him, Ēkāntada Rāmayya fought and vanquished them. He smashed the Jina and installed the <foreign>liṅga</foreign> <supplied reason="subaudible">in its place</supplied>.
            </p>
        </div> 
